  "prompt": "What is a good solar panel installation provider in Novato, California CA?",
  "response": "Finding a good solar panel installation provider in Novato, California, involves considering factors like experience, customer reviews, warranties, and the quality of products used. Here are a few reputable solar providers in the area:\n\n1. **SunPower by Stellar Solar**  \n   - **Why Choose Them?** SunPower is known for its high-efficiency solar panels and comprehensive warranties. Stellar Solar is a trusted local installer with years of experience in the North Bay area.  \n   - **Website:** [stellarsolar.com](https://www.stellarsolar.com)\n\n2. **Bell Solar Electric**  \n   - **Why Choose Them?** Based in Napa, Bell Solar Electric serves Novato and the surrounding areas. They offer custom solar solutions and have strong reviews for their customer service and installation quality.  \n   - **Website:** [bellsolarelectric.com](https://www.bellsolarelectric.com)\n\n3. **SolarCraft**  \n   - **Why Choose Them?** SolarCraft has been installing solar systems in Northern California for over 35 years. They offer a full range of services, including solar, battery storage, and energy efficiency upgrades.  \n   - **Website:** [solarcraft.com](https://www.solarcraft.com)\n\n4. **Renova Energy**  \n   - **Why Choose Them?** Renova Energy specializes in custom solar solutions and is known for its expertise in both residential and commercial installations. They also offer Enphase battery storage systems.  \n   - **Website:** [renovaenergy.com](https://www.renovaenergy.com)\n\n5. **Sunrun**  \n   - **Why Choose Them?** Sunrun is one of the largest residential solar providers in the U.S. They offer solar leases, power purchase agreements (PPAs), and purchase options, making solar accessible for many homeowners.  \n   - **Website:** [sunrun.com](https://www.sunrun.com)\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Provider:\n- **Get Multiple Quotes:** Compare proposals from at least 3-4 providers to ensure you\u2019re getting the best deal.  \n- **Check Reviews:** Look at online reviews on platforms like Yelp, Google, and the Better Business Bureau (BBB).  \n- **Ask About Warranties:** Ensure the provider offers robust warranties for both equipment and workmanship.  \n- **Local Experience:** Choose a provider with a strong track record in Novato or the North Bay area.  \n- **Financing Options:** Inquire about financing, leases, or PPAs if you\u2019re not planning to purchase outright.\n\nBy doing thorough research and comparing options, you can find a reliable solar provider that meets your needs in Novato.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
